# UI standards

The UI is a React + Vite SPA under `ui/src/`, using the `@/` alias (maps to `ui/src/`).

## File placement

| Kind | Location | Import from |
|------|----------|-------------|
| Root app + pages | `app/` | `@/app/...` |
| React components | `components/<feature>/` | `@/components` |
| API clients | `apis/` (+ endpoint paths in `apis/urls/`) | `@/apis` |
| Hooks | `hooks/` | `@/hooks` |
| `interface` shapes | `interfaces/*.ts` | `@/interfaces` |
| `type` aliases / unions | `types/*.ts` | `@/types` |
| Runtime constants | `constants/*.ts` | `@/constants` |
| Helpers (axios, storage) | `utilities/*.ts` | `@/utilities` |
| Global styles | `styles/` | imported in `main.tsx` |

Every folder has a barrel `index.ts`; add new public exports there.

## Interfaces & types

- Do not define `interface`, `type`, or exported prop aliases inside
  `components/` or `app/`.
- `interface` → `interfaces/*.ts`; component props use `I` prefix + `Props` suffix
  (e.g. `ITicketCardProps`).
- String unions / aliases → `types/*.ts` (e.g. `Locale`, `TicketStatus`).
- Unexported shapes used in a single file may stay local.

## Data fetching

- All HTTP goes through `apiGet`/`apiPost` in `@/utilities`, which attach the
  bearer token and unwrap the backend `{ status, entity }` envelope.
- Keep endpoint path strings in `apis/urls/`; keep call functions in `apis/`.
- SSE uses the native `EventSource` via `useTicketStream`; the token is passed as
  the `access_token` query param.

## Verification

```bash
cd ui && npm run tsc
cd ui && npm run build
```
